data_C2c_a


_vrf_PLAT088_C2c_a
;
PROBLEM: Poor Data / Parameter Ratio .................... 7.20 Note 
RESPONSE: The heavy disorder of the highly symmetric, perfluorinated 
aluminumalkoxide anions was treated appropriately using a disorder model with 
equal distance restraints for chemically equivalent bonds. The model is a 
compromise between data/parameter ratio and residual density. The occupancy of the 
anion disorder was kept on a fixed value to lower the number of parameters. Also the 
U values of the solvent molecule were refined isotropically. However, the highly 
restrained model led to a stable refinement and good low residual density.
;

 
